 pastry into sides and press to repair any splits in pastry. Trim overhanging edges with a knife. Place dish into refrigerator for 10 minutes to firm. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"content":"Line pastry case with baking paper and fill with rice, dried beans or pie weights. Place tin onto a large baking tray (30 x 40 cm) and bake for 10-15 minutes (160°C). Remove baking paper and weights and bake for a further 10-15 minutes (160°C), or until lightly golden. Set aside to cool completely."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Lemon filling"},{"content":"Place lemon zest into mixing bowl and chop <b>15 sec\/speed 9<b> or until finely chopped."},{"content":"Add sugar and mill <b>10 sec\/speed 8<b>."},{"content":"Add honey, lemon juice, cornflour, coconut milk, eggs and yolks and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 6<b>, until combined."},{"content":"Using a fine-mesh sieve, strain mixture into cooled pastry case and bake for 20-25 minutes (160°C), or until just set. Allow tart to cool completely in tin before serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Almond quinoa pastry can be substituted with Gluten-free goodness pastry (please refer to the recipe on this recipe chip).","If you prefer, you can use activated or roasted almonds instead of raw almonds in the pastry.","For a lovely flavour variation, you might like to substitute the lemon juice with half lemon juice and half lime juice. <p><\/p>"],"basicInfo":["medium","20m","2h 15m","12 portions"]}